# Portfolio and Investment Analysis

This project is part of the Quantitative and Digital Skills Portfolio for the Statistics II course.

## Project Description
The goal of this project is to analyze the stock performance of two companies, Coca-Cola and Netflix, using historical market data obtained from Yahoo Finance.

## Data
Weekly stock price data was downloaded from Yahoo Finance and organized in Google Sheets. The dataset includes weekly closing prices used to calculate stock returns.

## Methods
The following analytical steps were performed:
- Calculation of arithmetic returns
- Calculation of logarithmic returns
- Descriptive statistical analysis (max, min, range, mean, variance, standard deviation)
- Sharpe ratio calculation
- Regression analysis to examine the relationship between the stock returns

## Tools
- Google Sheets
- Microsoft Excel
- Yahoo Finance dataset

## Skills Demonstrated
- Financial data analysis
- Quantitative methods
- Spreadsheet modeling
- Descriptive statistics
- Regression analysis
